I"ë◊<img src="/assets/Logic/Effects/LogicEffects.png" alt="Logic Effects that are good">
<div class="image-caption">A selection of some awesome effects in Logic Pro X</div>

<p>It‚Äôs time for the Logic Effects review, finally! Sorry this has taken nearly an extra week, but we‚Äôre here now. I spent 55 hours specifically reading the effects manual, evaluating every plugin on a number of sources, testing with various analysis tools, reading the manual again, writing about plugins and editing this document. (I‚Äôm totally sick of it btw, jeez). That doesn‚Äôt include the time I‚Äôve spent so far just casually using the products. There may be an error here or there, so please let me know if you see one!</p>

<p>This time I‚Äôm doing the effects review differently than I have in the past (<a href="/music/2017/09/30/Review-of-Mixbus-effect-plugins.html">Mixbus Effects</a>, <a href="/music/2017/10/06/Review-of-Mixbus-instrument-and-MIDI-plugins.html">Mixbus Instruments</a>, <a href="/music/2017/06/27/Bitwig-Effects-review.html">Bitwig Effects</a>, <a href="/music/2017/06/29/Bitwig-Instruments-Review.html">Bitwig Instruments</a>, <a href="/studio/2017/02/08/Cubase-9-Audio-Effects-Review.html">Cubase Effects</a>, <a href="/music/2016/05/31/Studio-compOnents-review.html">Studio One Effects</a> and <a href="/music/2016/06/05/Studio-ContraptiOnes.html">Studio One Instruments</a>). Instead of rating every single plugin, I‚Äôm splitting the plugins in to 3 categories: Fantastic, Sufficient and Flawed. The categorization is decided as follows:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Fantastic</strong> - These are plugins that I think would be an excellent value to purchase if possible. Likewise, they compare favourably with third-party plugins on the market.</li>
  <li><strong>Sufficient</strong> - Sufficient get the job done without much hassle. There may be no fancy extra features like some third-party competitors, or maybe the DAW version is missing some common feature, but nevertheless it‚Äôs enough to get the job done.</li>
  <li><strong>Flawed</strong> - As the name implies, these plugins have some sort of flaw. I would suggest replacing these with a third-party product.</li>
</ul>

<p>Many of the plugins are vectorized for clean resizing and retina screens. I‚Äôve marked the non-vectorized models as of Logic 10.4.</p>

<p>There will be a total rating for everything included though, and that rating is‚Ä¶</p>

<p>Spoiler - Overall rating: <admrb rating="92"> </admrb></p>

